  "title": "2 · Background and Related Work",
  "paras": [
   "<h3>Background and Related Work</h3>",
   "<h3>Generating Marketing Creatives with Generative Models</h3>",
   "<p>Generated advertising content has crossed the quality threshold for practical use: in consumer studies, generative models can produce visual marketing content that matches or exceeds human benchmarks <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"hartmann2025\" data-cix=\"8\">[hartmann2025]</a>. Applied systems cover single-artifact production: AutoPoster generates advertising posters with automatic content-aware layout <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"lin2023\" data-cix=\"9\">[lin2023]</a>, reflective multi-LLM and multimodal agent pipelines generate advertising banners <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"wang2025mimo\" data-cix=\"10\">[wang2025mimo]</a>, and diversity-aware generation targets ad headlines <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"wang2025diver\" data-cix=\"11\">[wang2025diver]</a>. Beyond advertising, multi-agent collaboration is used for controllable image generation <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"ding2025muses\" data-cix=\"12\">[ding2025muses]</a>, iterative self-refinement improves automatic image design <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"yang2024idea2img\" data-cix=\"13\">[yang2024idea2img]</a>, and LLM-driven procedural content generation extends the same idea to game assets <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"tangUnreal2025\" data-cix=\"14\">[tangUnreal2025]</a>, the domain this thesis's task shape generalises to.</p>",
   "<p>Two strands come closest to the set problem. <c class=\"ref\" data-cid=\"consistory-setsim\">First, consistent text-to-image generation produces image sets with a shared subject or style, evaluated by averaging pairwise embedding similarity <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"tewel2024consistory\" data-cix=\"15\">[tewel2024consistory]</a>; second, coherence between text and images is studied for multimodal plan generation <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"lu2025textimageplan\" data-cix=\"16\">[lu2025textimageplan]</a>.</c> Neither varies the coordination structure that produces the set: consistency is achieved inside one generation process, not negotiated between agents. Work on multi-agent architectures for generation, in turn, studies capability and creativity rather than coordination granularity <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"lin2025\" data-cix=\"17\">[lin2025]</a><a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"chen2026\" data-cix=\"18\">[chen2026]</a>. The gap this thesis addresses sits exactly there: a fixed multi-artifact decomposition whose set-level coordination structure is the manipulated variable.</p>",
   "<h3>Evaluating Generated Visual Content</h3>",
   "<p>Automatic evaluation of conditional image generation has moved from opaque scores to explainable judge protocols. VIEScore rates semantic consistency and perceptual quality with sub-scores and rationales <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"ku2024viescore\" data-cix=\"19\">[ku2024viescore]</a>; VQAScore evaluates text-to-visual alignment through image-to-text generation <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"lin2024vqascore\" data-cix=\"20\">[lin2024vqascore]</a>; and InterleavedEval defines a holistic, reference-free protocol for interleaved text-and-image outputs, validated against human ratings by rank correlation <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"liu2024interleaved\" data-cix=\"21\">[liu2024interleaved]</a>. For text rendered inside generated images, perceptual text-quality assessment is an open problem of its own <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"koltsov2026tiqa\" data-cix=\"22\">[koltsov2026tiqa]</a>, which is why this thesis checks required claims by OCR instead of scoring text appearance (Chapter (→ch:evaluation-method)). Judge-based scoring inherits the biases of the judge: position, verbosity, and self-preference are documented and only partly mitigable <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"ye2025justice\" data-cix=\"23\">[ye2025justice]</a>, and pairwise judging flips more often than pointwise scoring under irrelevant distractor features <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"tripathi2025\" data-cix=\"24\">[tripathi2025]</a>. Both findings shape the coherence metric: pointwise whole-set scoring with randomised artifact order, and a judge validated against humans.</p>",
   "<h3>Human Evaluation Methodology</h3>",
   "<p>The human-evaluation protocol draws on three established findings. <c class=\"ref\" data-cid=\"cb07-ranking\">First, relative judgments are more reliable than absolute scales: ranking translation outputs was found more consistent and faster than five-point scoring, with the recommendation to replace scales with ranking <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"callisonburch2007meta\" data-cix=\"25\">[callisonburch2007meta]</a>.</c> <c class=\"ref\" data-cid=\"rankme-setup2\">Second, criteria scored together in one task correlate strongly and stop measuring separate things; separate elicitation lowers these correlations <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"novikova2018rankme\" data-cix=\"26\">[novikova2018rankme]</a>, and attribute scores correlate with overall quality at rank correlations of 0.78 to 0.96 in photo quality assessment <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"fang2020spaq\" data-cix=\"27\">[fang2020spaq]</a>.</c> <c class=\"chip ref\" data-cid=\"spaq-attrib\" title=\"spaq-attrib\">°</c> Third, evaluations need reliability reporting and bias control: inter-rater agreement statistics <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"artstein2008\" data-cix=\"28\">[artstein2008]</a>, best-practice guidance for human evaluation of generated content <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"vanderlee2021\" data-cix=\"29\">[vanderlee2021]</a>, and blinding, whose effect on judgment is documented for peer review <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"tomkins2017\" data-cix=\"30\">[tomkins2017]</a>. The A/B protocol and the separate rubric task (Chapter (→ch:evaluation-method)) implement exactly these three findings.</p>",
   "<h3>Reliability of LLM-Based Experiments</h3>",
   "<p>Single runs of stochastic systems are unreliable evidence. <c class=\"ref\" data-cid=\"blackwell-temp0\">Repeated evaluation shows that most evaluation slices invert at least one pairwise rank against a three-run majority, with the recommendation of at least two repetitions <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"alvarado2025repetitions\" data-cix=\"31\">[alvarado2025repetitions]</a>; benchmark results should be reported as distributions rather than single seeded runs <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"bouthillier2021variance\" data-cix=\"32\">[bouthillier2021variance]</a>; and measured run-to-run variation persists even at temperature zero <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"blackwell2024reproducible\" data-cix=\"33\">[blackwell2024reproducible]</a>.</c> <c class=\"ref\" data-cid=\"openai-seed\">Provider documentation states the same limit: seeds are best effort and determinism is not guaranteed <a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"openai2026seed\" data-cix=\"34\">[openai2026seed]</a><a class=\"cite\" data-src=\"anthropic2026api\" data-cix=\"35\">[anthropic2026api]</a>.</c> <c class=\"chip ref\" data-cid=\"anthropic-temp0\" title=\"anthropic-temp0\">°</c> The test matrix (three repetitions, recorded seeds, distribution-based comparison) and the reproducible harness follow directly from this literature (Chapters (→ch:design) and (→ch:implementation)).</p>"
  ]
